President Biden will host the United We Stand Summit to address the impact of hate-fueled violence on democracy and public safety. The summit aims to bring together Americans of all backgrounds to heal divisions and promote a shared vision for a more united America. Elected officials, faith leaders, and civil rights leaders have expressed support for the summit and emphasized the need for unity and respectful discourse. The summit will focus on combating hate-fueled violence, fostering safe political discourse, and finding common ground among different parties and communities. Various organizations and individuals have commended the White House for prioritizing this issue and have pledged their support for the summit's goals.